{"id":19112,"title":"Infectious endocarditis with five localisations--case reports.","abstract":"Infectious endocarditis is defined as an infection of the endocardial surface area of the heart which can include one or more cardiac valves, mural endocardium or a septal defect. We present the case of a patient, aged 8, hospitalized in Hemato-Oncology Department with pontine glioma, who was also diagnosed with infectious endocarditis in five locations.","date":"2014-04-18","categories":"Bacterial Infections and Mycoses","split":"test","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24741780","annotations":[{"name":"Endocarditis","weight":0.821349,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Endocarditis"},{"name":"Heart valve","weight":0.809594,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heart_valve"},{"name":"Endocardium","weight":0.79756,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Endocardium"},{"name":"Infection","weight":0.72904,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infection"},{"name":"Heart","weight":0.723286,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heart"},{"name":"Congenital heart defect","weight":0.678276,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Congenital_heart_defect"},{"name":"Septum","weight":0.392122,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Septum"},{"name":"Infectious disease","weight":0.386506,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infectious_disease"},{"name":"Patient","weight":0.378888,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patient"},{"name":"Congenital disorder","weight":0.345291,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Congenital_disorder"},{"name":"Valve","weight":0.0418302,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Valve"},{"name":"Glioma","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glioma"},{"name":"Area","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Area"},{"name":"Surface area","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_art